{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef\/set(buffered:)"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"title":"set(buffered:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib17IOChannelProtocolPAAE3set8bufferedySb_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib12IOChannelRefV"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref\/set(buffered:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A buffered channel can only be set unbuffered if the channel’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"internal buffers have been flushed. Newly created channels or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels which have returned "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"eof"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not require such a flush. For write-only channels, a call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"g_io_channel_flush () is sufficient. For all other channels,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the buffers may be flushed by a call to g_io_channel_seek_position ().","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This includes the possibility of seeking with seek type "},{"code":"cur","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and an offset of zero. Note that this means that socket-based","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"channels cannot be set unbuffered once they have had data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"read from them.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On unbuffered channels, it is safe to mix read and write","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calls from the new and old APIs, if this is necessary for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"maintaining old code.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default state of the channel is buffered."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelRef/set(buffered:)":{"title":"set(buffered:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef\/set(buffered:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The buffering state can only be set if the channel’s encoding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". For any other encoding, the channel must be buffered."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref\/set(buffered:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffered","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop."}],"title":"MainContext","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelRef/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref\/iochannelprotocol-implementations","role":"collectionGroup","title":"IOChannelProtocol Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef\/IOChannelProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/IOChannelRef":{"title":"IOChannelRef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"into the main event loop (see [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannelRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOChannelRef"}]}}}